.TH "xenbus_grant_ring" 9 "xenbus_grant_ring" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
xenbus_grant_ring \- 
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" xenbus_grant_ring
.BI "(struct xenbus_device *dev "  ","
.BI "void *vaddr "  ","
.BI "unsigned int nr_pages "  ","
.BI "grant_ref_t *grefs "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
xenbus device
.IP "vaddr" 12
starting virtual address of the ring
.IP "nr_pages" 12
number of pages to be granted
.IP "grefs" 12
grant reference array to be filled in
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Grant access to the given \fIvaddr\fP to the peer of the given device.
Then fill in \fIgrefs\fP with grant references.  Return 0 on success, or
-errno on error.  On error, the device will switch to
XenbusStateClosing, and the error will be saved in the store.
